\cf10 \cb2 Under pressure.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 And your system learned:\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 \'93I can do this.\'94\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 ---\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 ### Reframe\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 Automatic doesn\'92t mean fearless.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 It means familiar.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 Your body recognizes the pattern:\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf10 \cb2 anxiety shows up,\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf10 \cb2 you check,\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf10 \cb2 you move.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 No debate required.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 ---\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 ### Identity Shift\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 You\'92re not someone *trying* to be courageous.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 You\'92re someone who moves when discomfort appears.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 That\'92s already who you are.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 ---\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 ### Carry Forward\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 Nothing to add here.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf10 \cb2 Just notice it happening.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 Next chapter: what it means when you slip \'97 and why it doesn\'92t undo anything.\cf0 \cb1 \
