\cf10 ## CHAPTER 10\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 Slipping\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 # Experience: Slipping\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 You\'92re going to slip.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 That\'92s not pessimism.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf10 \cb2 That\'92s reality.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 You\'92ll avoid something.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf10 \cb2 You\'92ll hesitate.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf10 \cb2 You\'92ll back out.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 The mistake isn\'92t slipping.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 The mistake is deciding the slip *means something*.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 ---\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 ### Mechanism\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 Slipping triggers an old reflex:\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 \'93I\'92m back at the beginning.\'94\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 But that\'92s not how learning works.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 Skills don\'92t disappear because of one miss.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 Patterns don\'92t reset.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 ---\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 ### Reframe\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 A slip is a moment.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 Collapse is a story.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 You don\'92t need to correct the moment.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf10 \cb2 You need to refuse the story.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 ---\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 ### Identity Shift\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 Someone who slips and returns  \cf0 \cb1 \
\cf10 \cb2 is not failing.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 They\'92re trained.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 ---\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 ### Carry Forward\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 When the next slip happens:\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf10 \cb2 Notice it.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf10 \cb2 Name it.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf10 \cb2 Return to the next small move.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 That\'92s the work.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 Next: what actually changes when identity shifts.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
