\cf10 ## CHAPTER 11\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 Identity\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 # Experience: Identity Shift\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 Identity doesn\'92t change in a thought.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 It changes in evidence.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 You didn\'92t wake up different.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf10 \cb2 You acted different \'97 repeatedly.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 And eventually, the story caught up.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 ---\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 ### Mechanism\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 The brain updates identity based on behavior.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 Not affirmations.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf10 \cb2 Not insight.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 Action.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 Especially action taken under discomfort.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 ---\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 ### Reframe\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 You didn\'92t become someone new.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 You stopped organizing your life around avoidance.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 That\'92s it.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 ---\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 ### Identity Crystallization\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 You\'92re not \'93the anxious one.\'94\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 You\'92re the one who moves *with* anxiety present.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 That\'92s the identity you\'92ve already earned.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 ---\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 ### Carry Forward\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 This isn\'92t something to protect.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 It\'92s something to live.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf10 \cb2 Next: how to carry this forward without turning it into pressure.\cf0 \cb1 \
